{
  "text": "In this appendix, we derive the effective viscosities of compact objects that are summarized in Table V . Let us first compute the viscosities of non-rotating BHs [297, 298] with mass M . The membrane paradigm [CITATION_1] 299] (Color online) GW150914 upper bound on |\u03b1EdGB| in km derived by mapping the constraint on \u03b2 at \u22121PN order with each (\u03c71, \u03c72) allowed from the aLIGO measurement. Orange dashed lines show the allowed region from the effective spin \u03c7 eff measurement, while white curves show spins that shut off dipole radiation completely. However, note that the small coupling approximation used to derive these bounds is only valid within the region between the yellow curves.",
